NullsSortLast
/ Sorting a list that contains a null keeps every element (no drop, no throw) and orders the
/ null to the end — the last item of the sorted list is the null value.
- set %xs% = [3, null, 1]
- sort %xs%, write to %sorted%
- assert %sorted.Count% equals 3
- get last item from %sorted%, write to %last%
- assert %last% is null
